        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:49PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bennettsville, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 30 to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bennettsville, Mccoll, Chavistown, and Tatum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
